The paper deals with multi-agent systems and incentive design, which are core topics in the subfield of Multi-Agent Systems (cs.MA). The paper also discusses game theory and equilibrium concepts, which are relevant to the subfield of Game Theory and Economics (cs.GT). The use of reinforcement learning and black-box optimization suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the subfields of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper's focus on optimizing system performance suggests that it may also be relevant to the subfield of Control and Optimization (cs.SY).
